</i> ‘laurel’, although it is more probably of pre-Roman origin. The given name was moderately popular in the Middle Ages (when it was used for girls as well as boys), under the influence of a 3rd-century saint who was one of the seven deacons of Rome. He was martyred in  258 . The legend is that, having been required to hand over the Church's treasures to the civil authorities, he assembled the poor and sick and presented them. For this act of Christian defiance, he was roasted to death on a gridiron. In England the name is also associated with  St Laurence of Canterbury  (  d. 619 ). A more recent influence has been the actor  Sir Laurence Olivier  (  1907–89 ).  See also  Lawrence ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Lars Bjornsson was born about 1351, in Västergötland, Sweden. He had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with NN Trottesdotter. He died before 1 August 1386."},"et":{"abt 1351–bef 1 Aug 1386":"umbes 1351–enne 1. augustit 1386","–Female":"Surnud","1377–1455":"1377–1455","1379–1448":"1379–1448","–Male":"Surnud","1351–1386":"1351–1386","1448":"1448","1379":"1379","1455":"1455","1377":"1377","1386":"1386","1351":"1351","Abt 1379":"umbes 1379","abt 1351":"umbes 1351","abt 1377":"umbes 1377","bef 1 Aug 1386":"enne 1. augustit 1386","of Vastergotland,,, Sweden":"Västergötland, Rootsi","of Uppsl, Swdn":"Uppsala, Rootsi","Of,, Uppsala, Sweden":"Uppsala, Rootsi"},"fi":{"abt 1351–bef 1 Aug 1386":"noin 1351–ennen vuotta 1. elokuuta 1386","–Female":"Kuollut","1377–1455":"1377–1455","1379–1448":"1379–1448","–Male":"Kuollut","1351–1386":"1351–1386","1448":"1448","1379":"1379","1455":"1455","1377":"1377","1386":"1386","1351":"1351","Abt 1379":"noin 1379","abt 1351":"noin 1351","abt 1377":"noin 1377","bef 1 Aug 1386":"ennen vuotta 1. elokuuta 1386","of Vastergotland,,, Sweden":"Västergötland, Ruotsi","of Uppsl, Swdn":"Uppsala, Ruotsi","Of,, Uppsala, Sweden":"Uppsala, Ruotsi"},"fr":{"abt 1351–bef 1 Aug 1386":"environ 1351–avant 1 août 1386","–Female":"Décédée","1377–1455":"1377–1455","1